-- =============================================================================
-- INDEX SUMMARY
-- =============================================================================
--
-- Explicitly defined indexes (via ORM code):              42
--   - Column(..., index=True)  single-column indexes:     24
--   - __table_args__ Index()   composite indexes:         14
--   - __table_args__ Index()   named single-column:        3
--   - UNIQUE composite index:                              1
--     (rate_limit_counters: identifier + endpoint + window_start)
--   - GIN index (full-text search):                        1
--     (chunks.tsv_content)
--
-- Implicit indexes (auto-created by PostgreSQL, NOT listed above):
--   - Primary key indexes:         10  (one per table)
--   - UNIQUE constraint indexes:    4  (users.email, query_logs.query_id,
--                                       documents.source_file, vector_maps.chunk_id)
--
-- Total indexes on a live PostgreSQL instance:  ~56
--   (42 explicit + ~14 implicit from PK/UNIQUE constraints)
--
-- Note: Some explicit indexes duplicate coverage with implicit UNIQUE
-- indexes (e.g., ix_users_email duplicates the index PostgreSQL auto-creates
-- for uq_users_email). This is consistent with the ORM model definitions.
-- =============================================================================

